         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">22/3/80. ¶  ¶ The remarkable fungus, sent by you, dear Mr Ramsay, ¶ See M to E. Ramsay, 15March 1880(in this edition as 80-03-15a). ¶  ¶ belongs to the genus Clavaria, I think; but my means for mycolo...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">80.03.22</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To Edward Ramsay</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">ML MSS.562, Letters to E. P. Ramsay 1862-91, Mitchell Library, State Library of New South Wales Sydney.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">22/3/80.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>The remarkable fungus, sent by you, dear Mr Ramsay,<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn0" n="1">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>See M to E. Ramsay, 15<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>March 1880<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>(in this edition as 80-03-15a).</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>belongs to the genus Clavaria, I think; but my means for mycologic studies are here so limited both in books &amp; museum-specimens, that I do not like to give a positive opinion. I will send the specimen to a leading mycologist in England or Germany, Fries now being dead. Even if a fungus proves new for Australia, it may be known from other parts of the globe, the species having in many instances a wide and capricious distribution.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I wrote to Sir Sam. Wilson, who is so immensely rich &amp; who has such a taste for horticulture, to ask whether he would give £100 towards your collectors expenses, but he declines on the ground of the difficulty of really interesting new inland-fields being reached.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="">
                  <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn1" n="2">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Letters not found.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Regardfully your</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd. von Mueller.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Has your L.S.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn2" n="3">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Linnean<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Society of NSW.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>space for some notes on N. W. Austr. plants, which notes would occupy only some few Octavo-pages. They refer to the plants of the last portion of Mr Forrests expedition of last year. The specimens were lost sight off in the transmission &amp; only now turned up, too late for Mr F's Report.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn3" n="4">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>M's original intent had been to issue the list as an appendix to a report of John Forrest's<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>trigonometric<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>survey, but<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>publication of the survey was not approved by the WA Government, and<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>M's report<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>was issued as an independent publication,<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>B81.03.02<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>(M to J. Forrest, July 1879, and notes thereto).<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     </p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I suppose the notes could soon appear &amp; some extracopies of the print be struck off on my expense.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn4" n="5">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                           <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                        </seg>M's supplementary account was not given to the Linnean Society of NSW, but was<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>read to the Royal Society of NSW on 7 July 1880 and subsequently published in that<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Society's<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">Journal</seg>
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>(B81.13.04).</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
            </p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="plantnames"
               style="font-style: italic; font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Clavaria</p>
         </div>
